{"id":"lumc:rsmp:1.0.0","kmId":"rsmp","metamodelVersion":17,"name":"LUMC-DCC Software Management Plan","organizationId":"lumc","packages":[{"createdAt":"2026-05-10T22:54:13.259679Z","description":"A Knowledge Model for creating Software Management Plans (SMPs) ","events":[{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:27:40.575967338Z","entityUuid":"414f5370-df93-4b98-8289-58b881d81ceb","eventType":"AddKnowledgeModelEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","uuid":"ad839763-8bef-412f-9b5c-5145cc92397c"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:09.586Z","entityUuid":"a86be77f-e97d-49f9-a5f3-4af5105367e3","eventType":"AddChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","text":null,"title":"","uuid":"eb70a5e8-9a9e-42f8-910a-dbd34d2daa79"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:10.412Z","entityUuid":"a86be77f-e97d-49f9-a5f3-4af5105367e3","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"> Throughout the SMP, present-tense questions (\"Is…\", \"Does…\", \"Has…\") describe the intended state at the relevant project phase. For projects in planning, read these as \"is or will be\"; for active or maintenance projects, read them at face value. The phase tag on each question shows when the answer is normally expected to harden into a concrete reference.\n\nIdentify the project, the people responsible, and any external regulatory regime that applies. Keep this section short: detail belongs in the thematic chapters that follow.\n\nIf you're unsure about the management level (A / B / C) you've selected for the project, see the <> before proceeding."},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"General"},"uuid":"46f43142-cd9e-43ac-82ec-4c7e36bfdb0c"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:14.257Z","entityUuid":"2f8a5871-b095-4c59-962d-9609220c2f0a","eventType":"AddChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","text":null,"title":"","uuid":"0bdf31ec-93e3-48f7-9d3e-7323fe991e58"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:14.275Z","entityUuid":"2f8a5871-b095-4c59-962d-9609220c2f0a","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"Why does this software exist, and for whom? Funders, reviewers, and your future self all start here. Be concrete: prefer specific examples over abstract claims."},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Motivation"},"uuid":"13eef8e9-6dc2-41e6-904f-5682275e912e"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:18.573Z","entityUuid":"93c0dcb5-0d56-44af-8b2d-10c4fbef13ef","eventType":"AddChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","text":null,"title":"","uuid":"ee8edc57-c7b0-4084-b351-6ddb3186fc94"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:18.586Z","entityUuid":"93c0dcb5-0d56-44af-8b2d-10c4fbef13ef","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"Identify what can go wrong and decide what you'll do about it. This chapter is about risk awareness and proportionate mitigation, not risk prediction; you are not expected to enumerate every future failure mode, just the ones whose probability × impact is high enough that ignoring them would be reckless.\n\n**This SMP does not replace the LUMC Data Management Plan (DMP).** Data-protection details (legal basis, retention, DPIA outcomes) belong in the DMP. The Risks chapter only flags that the software touches such concerns and points to the right document or person."},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Risks"},"uuid":"bc0567fc-49d4-4f51-ab41-de5ce18cd159"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:24.773Z","entityUuid":"222b5f2e-0b72-4e5c-b1ec-ac1e5f88bacf","eventType":"AddChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","text":null,"title":"","uuid":"56487d9f-fe33-41b9-b778-afb9289d82db"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:24.787Z","entityUuid":"222b5f2e-0b72-4e5c-b1ec-ac1e5f88bacf","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"Plan resources for three phases of the software's life: development, maintenance, and retirement. Estimates are fine. The goal is to make resource needs explicit so that shortfalls are visible and not deferred."},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Planning"},"uuid":"bf5246b8-6a63-468a-a151-36545a33ffba"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:42.971Z","entityUuid":"d93d3f14-7bab-440c-8369-d9f6b299e976","eventType":"AddChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","text":null,"title":"","uuid":"5a5b8e6b-e2f9-4171-8db8-7c05e5fd2b95"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:28:43.003Z","entityUuid":"d93d3f14-7bab-440c-8369-d9f6b299e976","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"How do people find, retrieve and legally use your software? This chapter covers repository, registries, identifiers, citation, and the license."},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Licensing & accessibility"},"uuid":"5c1511cf-f0b8-4346-8b65-77bb549eeb7a"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:29:42.956Z","entityUuid":"bc0b7898-1dd3-4dc2-8879-ffa3f6ea4c8e","eventType":"AddChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","text":null,"title":"","uuid":"e416a778-dcc7-47b9-9acb-c816c4e9fcb4"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:29:42.981Z","entityUuid":"bc0b7898-1dd3-4dc2-8879-ffa3f6ea4c8e","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"Documentation is the most-cited reason that scientific software stops being usable. This chapter covers user-, deployment- and developer-facing documentation, plus the community artefacts that make collaboration possible (code of conduct, contributing guidelines, governance)."},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Documentation & community"},"uuid":"151f027f-8191-47df-944c-2756ab0ec245"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:29:54.721Z","entityUuid":"ba141448-f70d-4c95-b42c-be93a392936e","eventType":"AddChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","text":null,"title":"","uuid":"65ae8f89-ef54-4a8a-8a94-5a9b2c1b61e3"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:29:54.732Z","entityUuid":"ba141448-f70d-4c95-b42c-be93a392936e","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"How does the software talk to the rest of the world: which languages, which data formats, which platforms?"},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Interoperability"},"uuid":"ef32edde-87a7-408a-8cf9-b5fb79d80f77"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:30:00.537Z","entityUuid":"718c82b8-f655-4265-9b6d-b7e37e66ad6b","eventType":"AddChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","text":null,"title":"","uuid":"85652051-e574-462d-8d48-bf8132212702"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:30:00.548Z","entityUuid":"718c82b8-f655-4265-9b6d-b7e37e66ad6b","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"How do you (and a future maintainer) know the software still does what it is supposed to do? This chapter covers tests, CI, code quality, and the tooling that keeps a project reproducible."},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Testing & quality assurance"},"uuid":"971e0956-f786-436d-a788-3ffd650b0050"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:30:10.641Z","entityUuid":"f9f0867d-8ce4-4985-8c2c-966593149fdf","eventType":"AddChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","text":null,"title":"","uuid":"b4cfa6c3-7370-4379-a0e4-352d815516c8"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:30:10.655Z","entityUuid":"f9f0867d-8ce4-4985-8c2c-966593149fdf","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"How is the project versioned, released and distributed?"},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Versioning & release management"},"uuid":"90830008-f03b-4ee3-ad7c-e8ea64da2ba6"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:35:55.032Z","entityUuid":"68f0beb6-eaf7-4f1a-b7a3-b6cc0c875a38","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","parentUuid":"a86be77f-e97d-49f9-a5f3-4af5105367e3","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"text":null,"title":"","uuid":"23948ca7-d9ef-45c5-a4cb-db482d1e9583"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"answerUuids":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:35:56.073Z","entityUuid":"68f0beb6-eaf7-4f1a-b7a3-b6cc0c875a38","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"a86be77f-e97d-49f9-a5f3-4af5105367e3","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","referenceUuids":{"changed":false},"requiredPhaseUuid":{"changed":false},"tagUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":false},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Title"},"uuid":"f9927698-b454-4ade-9cd0-74f099bfd67f"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:36:00.476Z","entityUuid":"68f0beb6-eaf7-4f1a-b7a3-b6cc0c875a38","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"a86be77f-e97d-49f9-a5f3-4af5105367e3","questionType":"ValueQuestion","referenceUuids":{"changed":false},"requiredPhaseUuid":{"changed":false},"tagUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"Provide a clear, descriptive, unique title for the software: the name people use to cite, search and refer to it. Specific enough that someone unfamiliar with the project understands what it is broadly about; short enough to fit on a slide and a CLI prompt."},"title":{"changed":false},"uuid":"0128757f-e537-4f2a-9571-9c95057895f4","validations":{"changed":false},"valueType":{"changed":true,"value":"StringQuestionValueType"}},{"abbreviation":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:36:31.309Z","description":null,"entityUuid":"c23f39d1-907b-4a54-9add-51f7254b3561","eventType":"AddMetricEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","title":"","uuid":"9971e73a-e5b5-4b8c-b95e-46389988dfa1"},{"abbreviation":{"changed":true,"value":"FAIR-F"},"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:36:34.339Z","description":{"changed":true,"value":"How findable the software and its metadata are: by humans through search engines, by machines through indices, and by reviewers through stable identifiers.\n\n> The score is computed as: score = Σ(weight × measure) / Σ(weight) over all answered questions that contribute to this metric. Each answer's measure is set on the answer itself; weights are set per (question, metric) pair. Skipped questions don't count. The result is in [0, 1]; the SMP report renders it as a percentage. Treat metric scores as a navigation aid, not a certification."},"entityUuid":"c23f39d1-907b-4a54-9add-51f7254b3561","eventType":"EditMetricEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","title":{"changed":true,"value":"FAIR4RS - Findability"},"uuid":"44ff54f3-fe29-4131-a734-ae9bd8d3b883"},{"abbreviation":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:36:48.381Z","description":null,"entityUuid":"f6694694-75c5-443a-b925-c5d8480becf3","eventType":"AddMetricEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","title":"","uuid":"bfbe2cd0-9068-4f2b-ad43-1722e62db710"},{"abbreviation":{"changed":true,"value":"FAIR-A"},"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:36:48.401Z","description":{"changed":true,"value":"Whether the software is retrievable, by both humans and machines, using standard open protocols.\n\n> The score is computed as: score = Σ(weight × measure) / Σ(weight) over all answered questions that contribute to this metric. Each answer's measure is set on the answer itself; weights are set per (question, metric) pair. Skipped questions don't count. The result is in [0, 1]; the SMP report renders it as a percentage. Treat metric scores as a navigation aid, not a certification."},"entityUuid":"f6694694-75c5-443a-b925-c5d8480becf3","eventType":"EditMetricEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","title":{"changed":true,"value":"FAIR4RS - Accessibility"},"uuid":"6de2ec6d-8de7-43ad-beb6-07fadbae148b"},{"abbreviation":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:36:59.196Z","description":null,"entityUuid":"1f542bcf-d008-483e-a101-4509fb14fe81","eventType":"AddMetricEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","title":"","uuid":"232af9e7-2a8f-4082-8232-3e483383a29b"},{"abbreviation":{"changed":false},"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:36:59.218Z","description":{"changed":true,"value":"Whether the software's languages, formats, and interfaces are standard, documented, and machine-tractable enough to be combined with other tools.\n\n> The score is computed as: score = Σ(weight × measure) / Σ(weight) over all answered questions that contribute to this metric. Each answer's measure is set on the answer itself; weights are set per (question, metric) pair. Skipped questions don't count. The result is in [0, 1]; the SMP report renders it as a percentage. Treat metric scores as a navigation aid, not a certification."},"entityUuid":"1f542bcf-d008-483e-a101-4509fb14fe81","eventType":"EditMetricEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","title":{"changed":true,"value":"FAIR4RS - Interoperability"},"uuid":"cdd59bc5-0ed0-4051-98e3-f7cebdb4fb5c"},{"abbreviation":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:37:07.507Z","description":null,"entityUuid":"2a7fe444-029f-41e3-aae4-ae6b0645b4d4","eventType":"AddMetricEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","title":"","uuid":"f2721832-9ffc-4a7c-91f7-99b856fd3209"},{"abbreviation":{"changed":true,"value":"FAIR-R"},"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:37:07.528Z","description":{"changed":true,"value":"Whether someone else (or your future self) can install, run, modify, test, and cite the software.\n\n> The score is computed as: score = Σ(weight × measure) / Σ(weight) over all answered questions that contribute to this metric. Each answer's measure is set on the answer itself; weights are set per (question, metric) pair. Skipped questions don't count. The result is in [0, 1]; the SMP report renders it as a percentage. Treat metric scores as a navigation aid, not a certification."},"entityUuid":"2a7fe444-029f-41e3-aae4-ae6b0645b4d4","eventType":"EditMetricEvent","parentUuid":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","title":{"changed":true,"value":"FAIR4RS - Reusability"},"uuid":"94b95a80-7926-4aaa-ac74-a1aeedde4e7b"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:37:39.47Z","entityUuid":"c21e449e-8b43-403f-be68-dcb9e3abe7ba","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","parentUuid":"a86be77f-e97d-49f9-a5f3-4af5105367e3","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"text":null,"title":"","uuid":"f3e52a60-425b-4c89-a250-7599cd643995"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"answerUuids":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:37:40.504Z","entityUuid":"c21e449e-8b43-403f-be68-dcb9e3abe7ba","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"a86be77f-e97d-49f9-a5f3-4af5105367e3","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","referenceUuids":{"changed":false},"requiredPhaseUuid":{"changed":false},"tagUuids":{"changed":false},"text":{"changed":true,"value":"Is the development of the software funded?"},"title":{"changed":true,"value":"Funding"},"uuid":"5ca66d59-8ce4-4de2-a4c4-2ae4b444a8c2"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:38:02.073Z","entityUuid":"ef2a2194-5a5c-4eca-bac2-3d79fbeac9a7","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"","metricMeasures":[],"parentUuid":"c21e449e-8b43-403f-be68-dcb9e3abe7ba","uuid":"7e33f8d1-740b-4948-9e85-1af91417aeac"},{"advice":{"changed":false},"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:38:03.1Z","entityUuid":"ef2a2194-5a5c-4eca-bac2-3d79fbeac9a7","eventType":"EditAnswerEvent","followUpUuids":{"changed":false},"label":{"changed":true,"value":"Yes"},"metricMeasures":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"c21e449e-8b43-403f-be68-dcb9e3abe7ba","uuid":"6ba84fd7-2c01-4b62-885f-07901a4cec9f"},{"advice":null,"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:38:05.289Z","entityUuid":"12a33ddd-ff13-41ff-b84d-e04fb8f23400","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","label":"","metricMeasures":[],"parentUuid":"c21e449e-8b43-403f-be68-dcb9e3abe7ba","uuid":"81b17511-cffa-4936-b005-17f13ffcc10a"},{"advice":{"changed":false},"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:38:05.524Z","entityUuid":"12a33ddd-ff13-41ff-b84d-e04fb8f23400","eventType":"EditAnswerEvent","followUpUuids":{"changed":false},"label":{"changed":true,"value":"No"},"metricMeasures":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"c21e449e-8b43-403f-be68-dcb9e3abe7ba","uuid":"00401e2e-49bb-4201-9cc5-6a5d94661534"},{"annotations":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:38:12.856Z","entityUuid":"7ef49f2e-9981-421b-8a23-d1c5f181c741","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","parentUuid":"ef2a2194-5a5c-4eca-bac2-3d79fbeac9a7","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","requiredPhaseUuid":null,"tagUuids":[],"text":null,"title":"","uuid":"449cb53c-1146-4430-9b9b-a2c77c360536"},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"answerUuids":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2026-05-10T21:38:12.892Z","entityUuid":"7ef49f2e-9981-421b-8a23-d1c5f181c741","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"parentUuid":"ef2a2194-5a5c-4eca-bac2-3d79fbeac9a7","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","referenceU